    pearls: ["The 3 Cs of TCA toxicity: Convulsions, Cardiac conduction delays (wide QRS), Cardiovascular collapse","QRS duration is the BEST predictor of TCA toxicity severity: >100 ms = seizure risk; >160 ms = ventricular arrhythmia risk","Terminal R wave in aVR >3 mm is the MOST SENSITIVE ECG marker for TCA toxicity — look for this in all suspected overdoses","Sodium bicarbonate is the PRIMARY antidote — it overcomes sodium channel blockade AND increases protein binding of TCA through alkalinization","NEVER give flumazenil in suspected TCA overdose (even with benzodiazepine co-ingestion) — it removes the protective anticonvulsant effect of benzodiazepines and can precipitate refractory seizures","Phenytoin is CONTRAINDICATED in TCA-induced seizures because it also blocks sodium channels and worsens cardiotoxicity — use BENZODIAZEPINES only","TCA overdose can progress from alert to cardiac arrest within 1-2 HOURS — early recognition and aggressive treatment with sodium bicarbonate are critical for survival","Metabolic acidosis WORSENS TCA toxicity by increasing free (unbound) drug — correcting acidosis with sodium bicarbonate has dual benefit (sodium load + alkalinization)"],
