        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Stomatitis (oral ulcers/mucositis) is the most common side effect of mTOR inhibitors including everolimus. It can be managed with dexamethasone mouthwash (swish and spit), dose reduction if severe, and continued therapy. Discontinuation is reserved for severe or refractory cases, as stopping everolimus allows tumors to regrow."
